Vintage rugs are pieces previously owned by the maker of the rug who offers to sell it in order to buy something new or to help her household financially. All proceeds to directly to the makers of these rugs (check the Beni Ourain ones too, also made carefully by this family)

PLEASE READ: Today I visited a lovely family of a mother and her two daughters. They make rugs and sell them whenever they need to make little money to provide for themselves. . I had tea and food with them.. even though they had so little, they welcomed me with Moroccan tea, honey, bread, rice and milk and more..
I'm not a rug hunter or reseller who thinks about own profit. It breaks my heart to see anyone need anything. And so instead of buying the piece and selling them, I'm posting them directly to you. All proceeds go directly to these families.
Ps: there's a boucherouite (rags carpet) rug in their living room and only rugs all around.. they want to sell some rugs to be able to buy proper seatings for their sleeping and living area.
They'll be making new rugs which I'll be offering to help them consistently. Thank you for reading !!‚ù§

146 x 285 cm
About 5x9 ft

Here is another rare Stunner rare one of a kind rug curated by yours truly.. vintage rug connoisseurs would know! But please look around and compare! I pride myself in having a selection of artful genuine vintage berber rug from my moroccan berber community.

Zayania Vintage Rugs are A small but enthralling selection, (compared to a sea of unoriginal rugs on the platform)And clients tell me that :)

The color is a warm wheat tone and the patterns symbolize fertility and optimism.

The dark lines were made of natural dark sheep wool and the yellow saffron color from natural curcuma. Previous owner's mother made this 55 years ago

The photos don't do many of my rugs' justice. But when you receive a rug in person and feel the history in it you ll love it even more!

This Old vintage Azilal rug circa 1960 is directly from previous owner in Azilal high Atlas, Morocco. Berber relatives and friends in my community.
Pile: thin, soft medium-dark wheat, a beautifully vintage rug that'll last many decades more.


*most proceeds minus shipping and fees will go to previous owner.

If you have any questions or just a hello, don't hesitate I'm happy to respond!
